ome.smuggler.config.items

Class CryptoConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • ome.smuggler.config.items.CryptoConfig

  • public class CryptoConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    Specifies how to configure encryption of sensitive data. The available settings:
    • Whether to encrypt sensitive data. Optional parameter to specify whether sensitive data, such as session keys, should be encrypted: true for yes, false for no. Defaults to false if not specified, i.e. no encryption.
    • Encryption key. The key to use to encrypt data. This parameter is only used if encryption is turned on and, in that case, it must be set to a valid Base64-encoded key as generated by the exportKey method.
